==English==

===Etymology===
From Old (and modern) French [[généalogie]], from {{LL.}} [[genealogia]], from Greek [[γενεαλογία]], from [[γενεαλόγος]] ‘genealogist’, from [[γενεά]] ‘generation, descent’ + [[λόγος]] ‘student’.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}} ''(Note: spelling: not geneology)''
# The [[descent]] of a [[person]], [[family]], or [[group]] from an [[ancestor]] or ancestors; [[lineage]] or [[pedigree]].
# A [[record]] or [[table]] of such descent; a [[family tree]].
# The [[study]], and [[formal]] [[recording]] of such descents.

